<HEADLINE>
WILL EGOS GET IN WAY OF LAKERS' FATE? 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By BOB YOUNG  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The NBA's engraver has probably begun etching ``Los Angeles
Lakers'' on the  &UR; Larry O'Brien Trophy, which goes to the league
champion.
</P>
<P>
   Why not? Everybody else seems ready to concede a championship.
</P>
<P>
   And on paper, it sure looks as if the Lakers are the team to
beat now and for a long time to come with the deal that brought
them  &UR; Glen Rice from Charlotte.
</P>
<P>
   ``I get bitter and (ticked) off,'' Milwaukee Coach  &UR; George Karl
said. ``The Lakers get stronger. The Lakers are a very, very
powerful team. And they've gotten better.''
</P>
<P>
   Miami Coach  &UR; Pat Riley also said it was a great deal, noting
that forward  &UR; J.R. Reid, who also went to the Lakers, has been
Charlotte's best player this season.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Jerry West, executive vice president of the Lakers, has shown
again why he's regarded as one of the best personnel men in the
game. He got rid of  &UR; Nick Van Exel and signed  &UR; Derek Harper, he
fired  &UR; Del Harris and hired  &UR; Kurt Rambis, he shored up the club's
rebounding deficiency by adding  &UR; Dennis Rodman.
</P>
<P>
   With that, the Lakers already had a nine-game winning streak
going. And now, in Rice, he has a sharpshooter with a rattlesnake's
conscience.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think our bottom line was that we just didn't feel that we
had anyone here that could make shots on a consistent basis,
particularly when the game was on the line,'' West said.
</P>
<P>
   During a nine-year NBA career, Rice has averaged 20.8 points a
game. He has hit 41 percent of his three-point shots. There is no
more pure a shooter in the league.
</P>
<P>
   ``There are no excuses now,'' center  &UR; Shaquille O'Neal said.
``We've got to play and not talk about it. I've got my thug
(Rodman), my shooter (Rice),  &UR; Kobe (Bryant). Put that team down on
a piece of paper and it looks pretty darn nice. Now we've got to
apply it to the hardwood. I can't wait.''
</P>
<P>
   But there are a couple of things to keep in mind before awarding
that trophy.
</P>
<P>
   First, the Lakers still haven't won anything despite all of
their talent. This is O'Neal's seventh season in the league and
he's been to the Finals once.
</P>
<P>
   Second, why is Rice suddenly healthy?
</P>
<P>
   He didn't play a game for Charlotte, which had refused to pay
him what he wanted in a new contract, after undergoing arthroscopic
elbow surgery in January. Yet he pronounced the elbow 100 percent
healthy after the deal, and as if to prove it in his debut Friday
night, he hiked up 21 shots against Golden State.
</P>
<P>
   Finally, will everybody be able to get along?
</P>
<P>
   O'Neal wants the ball in his hands on the block. Bryant wants
the ball in his hands, creating off the dribble. And Rice wants it
in his hands behind the three-point line.
</P>
<P>
   Six hands, one basketball.
</P>
<P>
   ``Glen Rice is a great shooter, but he's a guy who needs the
ball,'' Orlando's  &UR; Nick Anderson told a reporter from the ``Orlando
Sentinel,'' echoing what many around the NBA are thinking. ``I
don't see how they're going to get enough shots for Shaq, Glen Rice
and Kobe Bryant.''
</P>
<P>
   They're not.
</P>
<P>
   But if Rice, O'Neal and Bryant accept that, the engraver might
as well get started. &QL; 
Nick's not so quick &QL; 
At least to get to practice.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Antonio McDyess wanted to play with Van Exel in Denver, and he
got his wish. But if the Nuggets made any assurances to Van Exel
about a new contract for his help in luring the Dice Man out of
Phoenix, you can bet the Nuggets are trying to figure out how to
fudge.
</P>
<P>
   Van Exel has been late for two practices now, including one the
day after a loss to the San Antonio Spurs.
</P>
<P>
   ``We can't come to practice late and stay out all night and
party,'' McDyess said.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, Van Exel, who is shooting 37 percent overall and 27.8
percent from three-point range, is supposed to be one of the
Nuggets' leaders.
</P>
<P>
   He had the nerve to do most of the talking in a team meeting
about the club's struggles. Surely the Nuggets know by now that
they're dealing with a con man. But he's got the same agent as
McDyess,  &UR; Tony
 &UR; Dutt.
</P>
<P>
   Good luck. &QL; 
Court vision &QL; 
 &UR; Sam Cassell, when asked about being traded just before he was sent
to Milwaukee in the massive deal that brought  &UR; Stephon Marbury to
New Jersey, wasn't worried: ``It doesn't bother me. . . . I can
play. I can hoop. Me and four blind (expletives) work.''
</P>
<P>
   Why not four blind teammates? With Cassell at point guard, they
would never see the ball anyway. &QL; 
See you in St. Pete &QL; 
 &UR; Charles Barkley, whose Rockets visit Phoenix tonight, told
reporters in Houston that when his Auburn Tigers make it to the
Final Four, he's going _ even if it means missing a game. And he's
planning on that happening.
</P>
<P>
   ``Auburn is going to the Final Four,'' he said. ``I'm going to
skip a game if they go to the Final Four. I'm going to the Final
Four. I don't care if we're playing the Lakers or anybody, if they
go to the Final Four, I'm going to be there. It's a
once-in-a-lifetime opportunity.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're probably going to win it all. We're the only team that
can beat Duke. The rest of them ought to just pack it in and let
Auburn play Duke. I have great admiration for Coach K  &UR; (Mike
Krzyzewski), but Auburn is spanking them.''
</P>
<P>
   At least the Rockets are off on March 29, the night of the
national final. &QL; 
How's that? &QL; 
March 23 marks the 20th anniversary of some quirky NBA history.
</P>
<P>
   It's the only time three players played for both teams.
</P>
<P>
   Actually, it all started in November 1978 when Philadelphia beat
New Jersey, 137-133, in overtime. But a protest of the game was
upheld by then-Commissioner  &UR; Larry O'Brien. The game was resumed on
March 23, 1979 with 5:50 to play in the third quarter.
</P>
<P>
   The Sixers won the game, anyway, this time, 123-117. But in the
interim between the start of the game in November and the finish in
March, the Sixers traded  &UR; Harvey Catchings and  &UR; Ralph Simpson to
the Nets for former Arizona star  &UR; Eric Money and  &UR; Al Skinner. The
names of Catchings, Simpson and Money appear for both teams in the
official box score. Skinner never got into the game for either
team. &QL; 
Includes information from other media sources. Bob Young can be
reached at 602-44-8271 or at bob.young(at)pni.com via e-mail. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
