<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NFK-FEATURE15-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    NEWS FOR KIDS: Britney Spears limps along while album soars
 &HT;    By Sonia Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The only thing that's been able to stop teen pop star Britney
Spears is dislocating her knee, which she is now nursing at her
Louisiana home.
</P>
<P>
   Britney Spears' sales are another matter altogether.
</P>
<P>
   As we call her for the sixth interview she's doing today, the
17-year-old has just learned that her first album, ``... Baby One
More Time,'' is No. 1 for the fourth week in a row.
</P>
<P>
   During her time off, we asked the singer to tell us what it's
like to go from ``Britney Spears, who?'' to ``Britney Spears,
star!'' in just over a month.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I read that right after you hurt your knee, you wheeled into
Cartier and tried on an $80,000 ring. What is it like to be able to
afford things like that now?
</P>
<P>
   A: Scary. I didn't buy it though. I was just window-shopping,
like I did before I had a record deal.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Is it true that you've wanted to be a star since you were 4
years old?
</P>
<P>
   A: I took dance lessons then, but the press has kind of been
getting that wrong. I didn't really know until I was in the fifth
grade.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Then you went to New York.
</P>
<P>
   A: Yeah, my mom moved with me for a year. It was really
different, coming from a small town (Kentwood, La.) and all. But I
did an off-Broadway play and some commercials. Then I got the
``Mickey Mouse Club.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: You were there when two members of 'N Sync and (`Felicity'
star) Keri Russell were doing it? Could you see them being who they
are now?
</P>
<P>
   A: We saw it in everyone.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Now that you're back home, how do your friends see and treat
you?
</P>
<P>
   A: The same. We still argue and act stupid and goof off and act
like sisters. If they didn't, I would kick their (butts).
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
