<P>
   FISH-PROTECTIONS (WASHINGTON) _ Dwindling salmon runs are
throughout the Pacific Northwest, from Ozette Lake on the Olympic
Peninsula to the Columbia, Snake and Willamette rivers. But, by the
end of the day Tuesday, virtually every watershed in Washington
state will be subject to the strictures of the federal Endangered
Species Act, which makes it a crime to harm endangered and
threatened species.
