THIS WEEK'S TV HIGHLIGHTS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
TODAY 
Rob Blake wants his teammates to know they still have a shot at the
playoffs. Right? If he says it enough times, maybe they'll finally
believe it. Ottawa at Kings, Fox Sports West, 7:30 p.m. 
TUESDAY 
No Rodman? No Marbury. So no problem. Lakers at Minnesota, Channel
9 and TNT, 5 p.m. 
WEDNESDAY 
Whatever happened to Ray ``Boom Boom'' Mancini? Seems like a biopic
(starring Tony Danza) waiting to happen. Until then, you'll find
Mancini doing cameo work, if anyone remembers him, on.... ``Two
Guys, a Girl and a Pizza Place,'' Channel 7, 8:30 p.m. 
THURSDAY 
Tonight's episode of the Fox Files _ it's the Murdoch Channel's
version of ``60 Minutes'' _ investigates drinking on college
campuses. They can go live tonight to bars in Phoenix and Knoxville
for the Sweet 16 spring-break blowout. NCAA men's basketball
tournament, regional quarterfinals, Channel 2 and DirecTV, 4:30
p.m. (Coverage continues Friday at 4:30 p.m., Saturday and Sunday
at 2:30 p.m. for the regional final doubleheaders). Mighty Ducks at
Kings, Fox Sports West, 7:30 p.m. 
 
 
FRIDAY 
Cris Collinsworth's freak show moves to a new night and, in this
episode, features the spaghetti-through-the-nose ``blow off.'' They
might consider changing the show's name, too. How about ``When Good
Sporscasters Suddenly Go Bad.'' ``Guinness World Records,'' Channel
11, 8 p.m. 
SATURDAY 
Holy Humberto, the Major League Soccer season is here already. The
Galaxy's season opener against Colorado, though, is relegated to
radio. New York-New Jersey at Miami, ESPN2, 5 p.m. 
SUNDAY 
My, look at how Rap Master Shaq has grown. We hardly recognize him
anymore. Say, how many NBA Finals you been to in L.A? !ital!Really?
Penny for your thoughts on how the Magic seems to actually be a
better team this year without you. Lakers at Orlando, Channel 4,
9:30 a.m. 

